WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:03.000
Abu Dhabi is the largest of the seven emirates that make up 

00:03.000 --> 00:07.000
the United Arab Emirates. It occupies nearly 87 percent of the country's 

00:07.000 --> 00:11.000
total landmass and includes the capital - the city of Abu Dhabi 

00:11.000 --> 00:15.000
- and a second major city named Al Ain, located near the 

00:15.000 --> 00:19.000
emirate's border with Oman. According to the 2005 census, the Emirate of 

00:19.000 --> 00:23.000
Abu Dhabi is home to over 1.3 million people, the majority of 

00:23.000 --> 00:27.000
whom are expatriates. 

